 Press |location=New York, NY |isbn=978-1-59558-993-4|pages=177\u201379|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last= Sen |first=Amartya |authorlink=Amartya Sen |editor=Eric J. Hobsbawm |title=Peasants in History: Essays in Honour of Daniel Thorner | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XscsAAAAMAAJ | year=1980 |publisher=Published for Sameeksha Trust by Oxford University Press |chapter=Famine Mortality: A Study of the Bengal Famine of 1943 |isbn=0195612159|ref=CITEREFA. Sen1980}}\n* {{cite book |last= Sen |first=Amartya |title=Poverty and Famines: An Essay on Entitlement and Deprivation |url=https://archive.org/details/povertyfamineses0000sena |url-access= registration |year=1981a |publisher=Oxford University Press|location=New York, NY|isbn=978-0-19-828463-5 |ref=CITEREFA. Sen1981a|at=(See chapter 6: [https://books.google.com/books?id=FVC9eqGkMr8C&pg=PA55 \"The Great Bengal Famine\"]).}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Sen |first1=Amartya |title=The Idea of Justice |publisher=Harvard University Press |location=Cambridge, MA |date=2011 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OM4RBAAAQBAJ|isbn= 978-0-674-06047-0 |ref=CITEREFA. Sen2011}}\n* {{cite book | first=Bhowani |last= Sen |title= Rural Bengal in Ruins |translator= N. Chakravarty |location = Bombay, India |publisher= People's Publishing House |oclc=27855268|year=1945 |ref=CITEREFB. Sen1945}}\n* {{cite book|last=Siegel|first=Benjamin Robert|title=Hungry Nation: Food, Famine, and the Making of Modern India|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kSVTDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA37|date=2018|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-1-108-42596-4|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv |last=Vernon |first=James |title=Hunger: A Modern History|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZPtV4cGU4LIC|date=2009 |publisher=Harvard University Press |location=Cambridge, MA|isbn=978-0-674-04467-8}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Yong|first=Tan Tai|title=The Garrison State: Military, Government and Society in Colonial Punjab, 1849\u20131947|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=y_iHAwAAQBAJ|date=2005|publisher=SAGE Publications|location=New Delhi, India|isbn=978-81-321-0347-9}}\n{{refend}}\n\n====Articles====\n{{refbegin |26em}}\n* {{cite dissertation| last=Ali |first=Tariq Omar |title=The Envelope of Global Trade: The Political Economy and Intellectual History of Jute in the Bengal Delta, 1850s to 1950s. |degree=Doctoral |url=http://nrs.harvard.edu/urn-3:HUL.InstRepos:10364584 |year=2012 |publisher=Harvard University | ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal |title = Land Reform Legislation in India | first = Konrad |last = Bekker |journal= Middle East Journal |volume=5 |number= 3 | date = Summer 1951| pages= 319\u201336 |jstor=4322295 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/ref/movies/1000best.html#D|title=The Best 1,000 Movies Ever Made |website=The New York Times |date=29 April 2003 |access-date=29 March 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160209060448/https://www.nytimes.com/ref/movies/1000best.html#D | archive-date= 9 February 2016 | url-status=dead | ref=CITEREFBest movies2003}}\n* {{cite journal |last= Bhattacharya |first=Sanjoy |title=Tackling hunger, disease and 'internal security': Official medical administration in colonial eastern India during World War II (Part I) |journal=The National Medical Journal of India |volume=15 |number=1 |pages=37\u201340 |year=2002a |url=http://archive.nmji.in/archives/Volume-15/issue-1/medicine-and-history.pdf |accessdate=8 February 2016 |ref=harv|pmid=11855591}}\n* {{cite journal |last= Bhattacharya |first=Sanjoy |title=Tackling hunger, disease and 'internal security': Official medical administration in colonial eastern India during World War II (Part II) |journal=The National Medical Journal of India |volume=15 |number=2 |year=2002b |url=http://archive.nmji.in/archives/Volume-15/issue-2/medicine-and-history.pdf |accessdate=8 February 2016 |pages=101\u201340 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal |last1=Bhattacharya | first1=Sanjoy | first2=Benjamin | last2=Zachariah | title='A Great Destiny': the British Colonial State and the Advertisement of Post-War Reconstruction in India, 1942\u201345 | journal=South Asia Research | date=April 1999 | volume=19 |issue=1 | pages=71\u2013100 | doi=10.1177/026272809901900105 | ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|last= Bose |first= Sugata |title=The Roots of 'Communal' Violence in Rural Bengal |journal= Modern Asian Studies |volume=16 |number=3 |year=1982b |pages= 463\u201391 |ref=CITEREFS. Bose1982 | doi= 10.1017/S0026749X00015274}}\n* {{cite journal |last1=Bose |first1=Sugata |title=Starvation amidst Plenty: The Making of Famine in Bengal, Honan and Tonkin, 1942\u201345 |journal=Modern Asian Studies |volume=24 |issue=4 |year=1990 |pages=699\u2013727 |doi=10.1017/S0026749X00010556 |ref=CITEREFS. Bose1990}}\n* {{cite conference|last=Bowbrick|first=Peter|title=How Sen's Theory Can Cause Famines|conference= Agricultural Economics Society Conference |date= March 1985 | url=http://www.bowbrick.org.uk/PB%20on%20Sen/atop.pdf |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Bowbrick |first=Peter |year=1986 |title=The causes of famine: A refutation of Professor Sen's theory |url=http://bowbrick.org.uk/Senpapers/Food%20Policy%20May%201986.pdf |journal=Food Policy |volume=11 |issue=2 |pages=105\u201324 |doi=10.1016/0306-9192(86)90059-X |access-date=1 September 2011 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Brennan |first=Lance |year=1988 |title=Government Famine Relief in Bengal, 1943 |jstor=2056974 |journal=The Journal of Asian Studies |volume=47 |issue=3 |pages=541\u201366 |doi=10.2307/2056974 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal | first1= Lance |last1= Brennan |first2= Les |last2= Heathcote |first3= Anton |last3= Lucas |year = 1984|title= The causation of famine: A comparative analysis of Lombok and Bengal 1891\u20131974 |journal= South Asia: Journal of South Asian Studies |volume= 7 |number = 1 |pages = 1\u201326 |doi= 10.1080/00856408408723049 | ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal |title=Political Mobilization in the Localities: The 1942 Quit India Mov